{
  "stem": "13063.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Very much so, more-- more than in any other time, especially comes to mind when I walked with my mother in a street in Borek.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A pack of the [INAUDIBLE], a pack of-- of Polish teenagers came over and demanded money from my mother, but she said, I didn't take any money.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they lit a cigarette, and-- and they burned my mother with a cigarette, with a-- with a lighted cigarette.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she was screaming from-- from pain, and I-- and I tried to-- to-- I don't know what I tried.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I tried to fend-- to fend them off, to protect her, and they beat me up.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a terrible, terrible experience that's stuck in my mind.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Did they say anything to you during--?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They called me dirty Jew.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's all.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And so-- this was routine, a routine call, a dirty Jew.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they left after they-- they saw that my mother didn't have any money, didn't take any money, didn't have any money.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they left, but not before subjecting her to such terrible pain and indignity, and me too, of course.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Happy, laughing, laughter.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 9 SECONDS] The former prime minister of Israel-- his name was Shamir, Yitzhak Shamir-- who was-- who was-- who is-- who is of Polish ancestry said that the Poles drank the hatred of the Jew together with their mothers' milk.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This is what he pronounced publicly, really.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And of course, immediately, there were protests from Poland, so he somehow wiggled out of it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But he knew what he was talking about.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This is what stuck-- quite possibly, but what stuck in my mind was this incident-- particular incident.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes, especially by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You see, the Germans did dirty work for the Poles.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
